.TH PODUP 1 "June 2026" "podup 0.16.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podup \- run docker-compose files on rootless Podman
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podup
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
[\fISERVICE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B podup
reads a Compose file (\fBdocker-compose.yml\fR or the compose-spec precedence
list) and translates it into rootless Podman operations over Podman's native
libpod REST API. It is a single static binary with no daemon and no Python
runtime, usable both as a standalone docker-compose replacement and as a Rust
library.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to the compose file. May be given multiple times to merge files in order;
later files override earlier ones. May also be set via \fBCOMPOSE_FILE\fR. When
unset, the compose-spec precedence list is probed in the current directory
(\fBcompose.yaml\fR, \fBcompose.yml\fR, \fBdocker-compose.yaml\fR,
\fBdocker-compose.yml\fR).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-project " " \fINAME\fR
Project name, used as a prefix for container, network and volume names. May
also be set via \fBCOMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME\fR. When unset, the top-level
\fBname:\fR field is used, then the sanitized basename of the project directory.
.TP
.BR \-\-socket " " \fIPATH\fR
Podman socket path. Overrides auto-detection and \fBPODMAN_SOCKET\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAMES\fR
Active profiles, comma-separated. May also be set via \fBCOMPOSE_PROFILES\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-project\-directory " " \fIPATH\fR
Base directory for resolving relative paths (env_file, build context, bind
mounts, config and secret sources). Defaults to the compose file's directory.
.TP
.BR \-\-env\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Additional env file loaded into the variable map used for interpolation. May be
given multiple times; later files win. The process environment and a project
\fB.env\fR still take precedence.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B up
Create and start all services. Options: \fB\-d\fR/\fB\-\-detach\fR,
\fB\-\-build\fR, \fB\-w\fR/\fB\-\-watch\fR, \fB\-\-remove\-orphans\fR,
\fB\-\-no\-recreate\fR, \fB\-\-force\-recreate\fR, \fB\-\-no\-deps\fR. Accepts a
trailing list of services to bring up (with their transitive depends_on).
.TP
.B down
Stop and remove containers. \fB\-v\fR/\fB\-\-volumes\fR also removes named
volumes declared in the compose file.
.TP
.B start
Start existing stopped containers.
.TP
.B stop
Stop running containers without removing them.
.TP
.B build
Build or rebuild service images.
.TP
.B rm
Remove stopped service containers. \fB\-f\fR/\fB\-\-force\fR removes running
containers (stopping them first).
.TP
.B kill
Send a signal to service containers. \fB\-s\fR/\fB\-\-signal\fR sets the signal
(default \fBSIGKILL\fR).
.TP
.B pause
Pause running service containers.
.TP
.B unpause
Resume paused service containers.
.TP
.B run \fISERVICE\fR [\fICOMMAND\fR...]
Run a one-off command in a new service container. Options: \fB\-\-rm\fR
(default true), \fB\-d\fR/\fB\-\-detach\fR, \fB\-e\fR/\fB\-\-env\fR KEY=VAL,
\fB\-\-name\fR, \fB\-\-service\-ports\fR.
.TP
.B cp \fISRC\fR \fIDST\fR
Copy files between a service container and the host. Use \fBSERVICE:PATH\fR for
the container side.
.TP
.B ps
List project containers.
.TP
.B top
Display the running processes of service containers.
.TP
.B port \fISERVICE\fR \fIPRIVATE_PORT\fR
Print the public binding for a container port. \fB\-\-proto\fR sets the protocol
(default \fBtcp\fR).
.TP
.B images
List images used by services.
.TP
.B logs \fR[\fISERVICE\fR]
View container output. \fB\-f\fR/\fB\-\-follow\fR streams new output.
.TP
.B exec \fISERVICE\fR \fICOMMAND\fR...
Execute a command in a running service container.
.TP
.B pull
Pull images for all services.
.TP
.B restart \fR[\fISERVICE\fR]
Restart services, or one named service.
.TP
.B config
Print the resolved compose file after substitution, extends and include.
.TP
.B generate quadlet \fR[\fB\-o\fR \fIDIR\fR]
Translate the compose file into Podman Quadlet unit files (one \fB.container\fR
per service plus \fB.network\fR and \fB.volume\fR units). Without
\fB\-o\fR/\fB\-\-output\fR the units are printed to stdout.
.TP
.B watch
Watch for file changes and sync, rebuild or restart services per the
\fBdevelop.watch\fR rules.
.TP
.B update
Update podup to the latest signed release. Verifies the release's Ed25519
signature against the embedded public key and its SHA-256 checksum, failing
closed. \fB\-\-check\fR only reports whether a newer release exists;
\fB\-\-force\fR reinstalls even when not newer.
.TP
.B completions \fISHELL\fR
Print a shell completion script to stdout for \fBbash\fR, \fBzsh\fR, \fBfish\fR,
\fBpowershell\fR or \fBelvish\fR. The Debian package installs the bash, zsh and
fish scripts automatically.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B COMPOSE_FILE
Path-separator-delimited list of compose files (see \fB\-\-file\fR).
.TP
.B COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME
Default project name (see \fB\-\-project\fR).
.TP
.B COMPOSE_PROFILES
Default active profiles (see \fB\-\-profile\fR).
.TP
.B PODMAN_SOCKET
Podman socket path (see \fB\-\-socket\fR).
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Log verbosity filter. With no value set, warnings and errors are shown; set
e.g. \fBRUST_LOG=podup=info\fR or \fBRUST_LOG=podup=debug\fR for more detail.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
A command failed (for example a parse error or a Podman error).
.TP
.B 2
\fBupdate\fR failed to verify or install a release.
.PP
\fBrun\fR propagates the container's own exit code verbatim, so any other
non-zero status comes from the container that was run.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B docker-compose.yml
Default compose file when none is given.
.TP
.B .env
Project environment file, loaded for variable interpolation.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR podman (1),
.BR podman-systemd.unit (5)
.PP
Full documentation at: \fIhttps://github.com/Glyndor/podup\fR
